Advantages over the `.split(...)[0]`-type answers:

 1. It directly does exactly what is being asked, i.e. &quot;Find the first sequence of non-space characters.&quot; So the self-documentation is more explicit.

 2. It is more efficient when called on multiple strings (e.g. for batch processing a large list of strings) because the regular expression is compiled only once.

 3. It is more space-efficient because it avoids unnecessarily creating a whole array with references to each word when we only need the first.

 4. It works without having to trim the string.

